This is soooooo easy to make. It gets costlier the more lux you want it but the core ingredients like oats, linseed, millet flakes etc are mixed with a touch of syrup (healthy options or even simple golden syrup) and baked till brown and crunchy. When I make it, I make a huge batch with toasted nuts (cashew, almond, pine nuts, etc), sesame seeds, toasted coconut flakes... whatever I want and it lasts for ages but for the fact that everyone eats it it so fast. The nuts can make it more costly but really if you go for it and make a big batch, you will have it for breakfast, snack handfulls and anything else you want for ages. Of course, you can make a gluten free variety. I just haven't. My mother made it all the time when we were children. It's a 1970s staple.
